      "id": "Q18",
      "page": 3,
      "dimension": "output_content",
      "text": "This is especially relevant when measuring unintended bias, because in real-world data, the amount of examples in each identity subgroup, and the balance between negative and positive examples can vary widely across groups (in fact, this variation is often a source of bias)."
