    {
      "id": "Q19",
      "page": 3,
      "dimension": "output_form",
      "text": "Enforcing that for each AUC, either all negative or all positive examples (or both in Subgroup AUC) come from one identity group, means that mis-orderings involving that particular subset cannot be drowned out by results from other groups, ensuring that these metrics are robust to data imbalances likely to occur in real data."
